          "raw": "{\r\n  \"title\": \"Implementing Pagination for High-Performance APIs\",\r\n  \"content\": \"Pagination is an essential feature for APIs that return large datasets. Without pagination, endpoints that return thousands of records can overload the server and degrade performance.\\n\\nA common pagination strategy uses SQL LIMIT and OFFSET clauses. The client specifies the page number and the number of records per page, and the backend calculates the offset accordingly.\\n\\nIn addition to returning paginated data, APIs should also return metadata such as total record count and total pages. This information helps clients build better user interfaces.\\n\\nProper pagination improves response times and reduces memory usage on the server.\\n\\nBy implementing pagination correctly, backend systems remain performant even as data volume increases.\"\r\n}\r\n",
